<TITLE>Glow Text</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<H1>GlowText</H1>
<P>The GlowText applet is an applet which allows you to make a particular
piece of text glow when the mouse pointer is over it:
here is some text which is
<APPLET CODE="GlowText" HEIGHT="18" WIDTH="50" ALIGN="absbottom">
<PARAM NAME="text" VALUE="glowing.">
<param NAME="fgcolor" VALUE="#0000ff">
<param NAME="bgcolor" VALUE="#ffffff">
<param NAME="tocolor" VALUE="#ff0000">
<param NAME="href" VALUE="http://www.hway.net/edd/">
<param NAME="font" VALUE="TimesRoman">
<param NAME="fontsize" VALUE="14">
<param NAME="fontstyle" VALUE="PLAIN">
glowing.
</APPLET></P>
<P>This piece of text can also act as a hyperlink and take the browser
to another location when clicked upon.</P>
<P>The font and colors of the text are completely customizable - it's
up to you to make sure they look OK! Here's a breakdown of the applet parameters
and their possible values.</P>
<P><TABLE BORDER=1>
<TR>
<TH>Parameter</TH><TH>Description</TH><TH>Allowed values</TH><TH>Default (value if parameter omitted)</TH>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>text</TD><TD>The text which will glow</TD><TD>Any string</TD><TD>GlowText</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>fgcolor</TD><TD>The color of the text</TD><TD>A Netscape style hex color string, e.g. #ff0000 for red</TD><TD>#000000</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>tocolor</TD><TD>The color the text glows</TD><TD>As for <i>fgcolor</i></TD><TD>#fffffff</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>bgcolor</TD><td>The background color of the applet</td><TD>As for <i>fgcolor</i></td><TD>transparent</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>href</TD><TD>A link to jump to when the text is clicked on</TD><TD>A fully qualified proper URL</TD><TD>none</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>font</TD><TD>The font to use for the text</TD><TD>A Java fontname (TimesRoman, Courier or Helvetica)</TD><TD>the Java default font</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD>fontsize</TD><TD>The point size of the text</TD><TD>A number</TD><TD>If not specified, then the Java default font is again used</TD>
</TR>
<TD>fontstyle</TD><TD>The style of the text font</TD><TD>BOLD, ITALIC, BOLDITALIC, PLAIN</TD><TD>PLAIN</TD>
</TABLE></P>
<P>Here's the tag used for the applet in the first paragraph of this page:</P>
<PRE>
&lt;APPLET CODE="GlowText" HEIGHT="18" WIDTH="50" ALIGN="absbottom"&gt;
&lt;PARAM NAME="text" VALUE="glowing."&gt;
&lt;param NAME="fgcolor" VALUE="#0000ff"&gt;
&lt;param NAME="bgcolor" VALUE="#ffffff"&gt;
&lt;param NAME="tocolor" VALUE="#ff0000"&gt;
&lt;param NAME="href" VALUE="http://www.hway.net/edd/"&gt;
&lt;param NAME="font" VALUE="TimesRoman"&gt;
&lt;param NAME="fontsize" VALUE="14"&gt;
&lt;param NAME="fontstyle" VALUE="PLAIN"&gt;
glowing.
&lt;/APPLET&gt;
</PRE>
<P>
The best way to make sure the baseline of the text in the applet lines up
with the text in the page is to use <TT>absbottom</TT> for <TT>ALIGN</TT> and
adjust the <TT>HEIGHT</TT> of the applet until everything seems OK. This works
because the text is always printed at the bottom-left of the applet. Be aware
that it may go horribly wrong on a browser different to yours anyway!    
</P>
<H2>Downloading</H2>
<P>
If you wish to use this applet, you can either download the
<A href="GlowText.java">source code</A>, or the 
<A href="GlowText.class">compiled .class file</A> (shift-click for the
.class file!). Simply put
the .class file in the same directory as the HTML file you wish
to use it with. Enjoy!
</P>
